properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 15 at 10:02PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
Strong and gusty southeast winds will develop along Turnagain Arm
and the Anchorage Hillside during the day Monday and peak Monday
night. Gusts as high as 70 mph are likely Monday night. Gusty east
to southeast winds will also move into the rest of Anchorage and
much of the Matanuska Valley Monday night. Winds could gust as
high as 20 to 35 mph. The arrival of winds will cause
temperatures across the area to jump above freezing, possibly
reaching the upper 30s to lower 40s. Winds are expected to then
die down during the day Tuesday, with temperatures cooling back
down to freezing or below.

There is still some uncertainty in the track and strength of the
storm system causing these winds. Stay tuned to the latest forecasts
for this impending storm system by visiting weather.gov/afc.

NWSheadline: Gusty winds and warm temperatures will likely return to Anchorage and the Matanuska Valley late Monday into Tuesday
